Definition: weak and likely to lose consciousness
Example: suddenly felt faint from the pain; was sick and faint from hunger; felt light in the head; a swooning fit; light-headed with wine; light-headed from lack of sleep
Synonyms: noun, event, feeling, faintness, light, swooning, light-headed, lightheaded, state, lightheadedness, weak, and, likely, to, lose, consciousness, suddenly, felt, from, the, pain, was, sick, hunger, in, head, a, fit, with, wine, lack, of, sleep
Category: adj.all
